The paper presents a method for face recognition using a biologically plausible model of information processing, which involves the use of neural networks. This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper's focus on developing an autonomic system for face recognition suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of information processing models could also place it in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
